{
  "texts": [
    "One way to achieve this is to utilize unsupervised and selfsupervised learning for pre-training of image features on unlabeled data.",
    "In self-supervised learning, the data itself is used to generate the supervisory information to guide the training.",
    "Typically, this is done by generating augmented versions of the images to obtain image pairs that have the same label.",
    "Image features learned this way can then be fine-tuned for the target dataset with a small amount of labeled training data using transfer learning.",
    "Large variation between plankton image datasets with different species compositions and imaging instruments can be considered not only a challenge but also an opportunity."
  ]
}